In Apples to Apples, there 

> Players start with a hand of seven "red apple" cards, which feature
> nouns. A player is selected to be the first judge, and that judge
> plays a "green apple" card, which features an adjective. The round
> is won by playing the "red apple" card that the judge determines to
> be the best match for the "green apple" card. The role of the judge
> rotates, and the number of rounds is determined by the number of
> players.